description: Numbers that are divisible by exactly 5 different primes.
links: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: 2730 = 2*3*5*7*13 is the first nontrivial 5-prime factor number following the 5th primorial, 2310 = 2*3*5*7*11.
mathematica: lst={};Do[If[Length[FactorInteger[n]]==5, (*Print[n];*)AppendTo[lst, n]], {n, 3*10^4}];lst (* _Vladimir Joseph Stephan Orlovsky_, Aug 21 2008 *)Select[Range[12000],PrimeNu[#]==5&] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Feb 13 2012 *)
